Hi Bill,

Do not use ProcessCTDdata.job.  I used it in the beginning.  Then I stopped.

The ProcessRSNdata.job is the script that will process the incoming CTD (1st) and RSN (2nd) data every 15 minutes.  More of that later.

To Stop all the CTD processing, you and Brian need to suspend the SaveCTDdata.job script.

The SaveCTDdata.job is used once a day to save the CTD data collected during the day into the long-term save file plus update the long-term graphs.

To stop the daily every 15 minutes CTD data processing, you and Brian need to edit the ProcessRSNdata.job script by removing or commenting out the 3 or 4 CTD commands at the top of the file.  I cannot remember the commands.  But they should be easily recognized by looking for the words "CTD"s.

By the way, there is a file called ProcessRSNdata.Job with the Capital J in the suffix.  That file is a copy of the file: ProcessRSNdata.job (please check to make sure).  So when you are ready to resume the CTD processing, just copy ProcessRSNdata.Job to ProcessRSNdata.job (for recovering the removed CTD processing commands).

Hope that helps.

--Andy

